<TITLE> Minister warns against fertiliser 'fixing' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jamalpur, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com)  The government will take strict steps against any manipulation of fertiliser stocks, the industries minister warned on Tuesday. The government has ensured adequate stocks through production and imports, minister Dilip Barua said. "So there should not be any shortage of fertiliser over the next Irri-Boro season," he said. He was speaking at a views exchange meeting at Sarishabari Upazila in Jamalpur, after visiting the stat-run Jamuna Fertiliser Factory. The minister said the government was moving to install a Urea Plant at the Jamuna factory. Fertiliser factories across the country would also be fully manned, he said, assuring all vacancies would be filled. Bangladesh Chemical Industries Corporation chairman KH Masud Siddique, among others, also attended the meeting. bdn
